8/23/2020

Parents, Guardians, and Students,

The Woodlawn School District remains in constant contact with the Arkansas Department of Health and Division of Elementary and Secondary (DESE) Division regarding the safety and wellbeing of the Woodlawn School District on matters related to COVID-19. Due to recent events, the Woodlawn School District will delay the start of school pending ADH guidance to allow staff the opportunity to receive COVID-19 testing. This precaution allows our district to ensure the safety of students and other staff members. We would rather be over cautious rather than not in this case. We apologize for any inconveniences, but your children and the staffâ€™s safety are our top priority.

Please Do Not Bring Your Children To The School Tomorrow Until Further Notice, and continue to watch for updates on the Woodlawn School District webpage and eNote notifications. Questions or concerns may be directed to the central office at 870-357-8108.

Thank you for your patience and understanding.

Dudley Hume, Superintendent
Woodlawn School District

Diplomas not picked up during the ceremony will be available for the student to pick up at the high school office beginning Monday, July 20.

Rick from Herff Jones will be at the school tomorrow, April 1st from 2-4 to hand out cap and gown orders. Only the senior or parent may pick up the order.

Orders will be handed out at the front entrance. Students will drive through and remain in their vehicles.

All balances must be paid in full at the pick up. Text Rick at 5013188126 for balances or payment questions and include your name and school.

If you are not able to pick up your order tomorrow contact the high school office to schedule a pick up time for another day.
